The PCA performed with the proportions of hind- and forelimb bones (Table 2 ;
Figure 6
) produced two principal components explaining 72.1 % of the total variance. 43.9 % is explained by PC 1 , which shows a high positive weighting for ulna and femur lengths, and a high negative weighting for tarsometatarsus and carpometacarpus. PC 2 explained 28.2 % of the variance and shows a high positive weighting for humerus length, and a high negative weighting for carpometacarpus and ulna.
